ent.description: Wat Arun, also known as the Temple of Dawn, is a Buddhist temple located on the west bank of the Chao Phraya River in Thonburi, Bangkok. Renowned for its towering spires, also known as prangs, intricately decorated with colorful porcelain and seashells, the temple's central prang rises approximately 79 meters high. The temple's architecture reflects a blend of Khmer and Thai styles, and it serves as both a place of worship and a symbol of Bangkok's rich cultural heritage.

description.div: Thonburi is one of the 50 districts (khet) of Bangkok, Thailand, located at the west bank of the Chao Phraya River.
